table.name: email_list
table.Comment: List of users to email when program updates

table.name: update_procedure
table.Comment: Used to updated pySMS remotely. Stores update procedures for file moving and other functions

table.name: billing
table.Comment: Actual billings from the SMS compliance tool

table.name: case_table
table.Comment: SMS Cases

table.name: ci_billing_parameters
table.Comment: Static Parameters used by the SMS Compliance Tool

table.name: ci_extensions_due_back
table.Comment: Within the SMS Compliance tool, this table represents the Implant Bank extension/return orders that have not been returned. Populated by generate_ci_inbound_outbound()

table.name: ci_extensions_returned
table.Comment: Within the SMS Compliance tool, this table represents the Implant Bank extension/return orders that have already been returned. Populated by generate_ci_inbound_outbound()

table.name: ci_order_line_summary
table.Comment: The finalized output, at a detail (line) level, for the SMS Compliance Tool. Populated by generate_ci_inbound_outbound()

table.name: ci_shipments_due_back
table.Comment: Within the SMS Compliance tool, this table represents the Implant Bank return orders that have not been returned. Populated by generate_ci_inbound_outbound()

table.name: ci_shipments_out
table.Comment: Within the SMS Compliance tool, this table represents the Implant Bank outbound orders that have shipped from Southaven to the territory. Only the orders in this table have freight charges associated with them. Populated by generate_ci_inbound_outbound()

table.name: ci_shipments_returned
table.Comment: Within the SMS Compliance tool, this table represents the Implant Bank return orders that have been returned. Populated by generate_ci_inbound_outbound()

table.name: contact_names
table.Comment: A list of territories and account number / ship to codes used by the billing module of the SMS Compliance Tool

table.name: distributor
table.Comment: SMS Distributors

table.name: enum
table.Comment: A list of various enumerations that Bo has provided to us to demistify some of the integer fields within various SMS tables

table.name: fedex_rates
table.Comment: Fed Ex shipping rates, manually provided and updated from Andrea Regan for use in the SMS Compliance tool

table.name: freight_override
table.Comment: Overrides for use by the SMS Compliance Tool. Any package listed in this table will have the freight value and/or ship via code overridden. This enables manual corrections to specific records in SMS for billing purposes without having to alter data of record

table.name: holidays
table.Comment: A list of holidays, used in work-day calculations within the SMS compliance tool. This table feeds into the weekly creation of the util.work_days table

table.name: loaner_pool_hold_notes
table.Comment: Notes entered into the Loaner Pool Holds applet of the DCS Utilities application

table.name: loaner_pool_holds
table.Comment: A daily replication of the Loaner Pool Holds report from SMS, filtered for specific use in the Loaner Pool Hold Notes applet of DCS Utilities. POC is Lana Hunter

table.name: lp_late_items_current
table.Comment: The current Loaner Pool Late Items report from SMS, Tammy Davis, 10/25/2012

table.name: lp_late_items_history
table.Comment: A historical snapshot of all lines from the Loaner Pool Late report from SMS, along with the "last_report_date," or last time we saw that line of data on the report, giving us a clue as to how late it was when it was returned. Created 10/25/2012. Prior to 4/15/13, this report was captured from the Excel reports out of SMS. After that, the data is pulled from a query that runs on GIWPRD1
